<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3871.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "87" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2014-10-06" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "3871" ;
    dc:creator "Carpintero, Diego Leonardo" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Western Hemisphere Lasiochilinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Anthocoridae) with comments on some extralimital species and some considerations on suprageneric relationships" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947861>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947945>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947947>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947949>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947951> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947861>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–16. Left metapleura of different genera of Lasiochilinae showing the ostiolar peritreme and metapleural microsculpture. 1–2, Plochiocoris (350X and 1000X respectively); 3–5, Eusolenophora (350X, 1000X and 2000X); 6–9, two species of Lasiocolpus showing the small specific differences following a generic pattern: 6–7, L. minor (200X and 1000X) and 8–9, L. sinuaticollis (200X and 1000X); 10–12, Anaelia (200X, 1000X and 2000X); 13–14, Dilasia (200X, and 2000X); 15–16, Lasiochilus (200X, and 2000X)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947945>
    dc:description "FIGURES 195–199. Species of genus Lasiochilus. 195, L. (L.) colpoides Female, holotype (3.12 mm); 196, L. (S.) duckei Female, holotype; 197, L. (L.) hirtellus Male (3.08 mm); 198, L. (L.) pallidulus Female; 199, Idem. Female, holotype (2.63 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947945/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947947>
    dc:description "FIGURES 201–214. L. (L.) colpoides. Male. 201, Head; 202, Pronotum; 203, Foretibia showing the teeth (Te) on internal margin and pad (Fos); 204, Apical half of foretibia; 205, Teeth on foretrochanter (Tte); 206, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternum (Ms); 207, Brachycerous hemelytron; 208, Copulatory teeth (Cte); 209, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 210, Detail of left paramere. Female. 211, Macrocerous hemelytron; 212, Genitalia showing parietovaginal gland (PG); 213, Row of hairs (Rha) in the centre of every urosternite; 214, Detail of parietovaginal gland (PG)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947947/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947949>
    dc:description "FIGURES 215–216. L. (L.) hirtellus. Male. 215, Copulatory teeth (Cte); 216, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947949/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947951>
    dc:description "FIGURES 217–231. L. (L.) pallidulus. Male. 217, Head; 218, Pronotum; 219, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) on internal margin, teeth on foretrochanter (Tte) and pad (Fos); 220, Apical half of foretibia; 221, Teeth on foretrochanter; 222, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternum (Ms); 223, Hemelytron; 224, Detail of punctures of hemelytron; 225, Copulatory teeth (Cte); 226, Detail of copulatory teeth (Cte); 227, Last abdominal segments showing left paramere (LP) and copulatory teeth (Cte); 228, Detail of left paramere. Female. 229, Genitalia showing punctures (Pfg) and parietovaginal gland (PG); 230, Detail of punctures on centre of VII sternite; 231, Detail of parietovaginal gland." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947951/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

